import React from 'react'
  import { MDXTag } from '@mdx-js/tag'
  import {Playground, PropsTable} from 'docz';
import BwkzButton from './BwkzButton';

export default ({components, ...props}) => <MDXTag name="wrapper"  components={components}>
<MDXTag name="h1" components={components} props={{"id":"bwkzbutton"}}>{`BwkzButton`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="h3" components={components} props={{"id":"the-default-view"}}>{`The default view`}</MDXTag>
<BwkzButton>
  BwkzButton
</BwkzButton>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}><MDXTag name="em" components={components} parentName="p">{`This is the default view placed with no additional options included.`}</MDXTag></MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="h3" components={components} props={{"id":"examples"}}>{`Examples`}</MDXTag>
<BwkzButton
  borderColor="#eee"
  borderRadius="1em"
  backgroundColor="#F5F2F0"
  color="#E04B69"
>
  BwkzButton
</BwkzButton>
<MDXTag name="h3" components={components} props={{"id":"search-bar-props"}}>{`Search Bar Props`}</MDXTag>
<PropsTable of={BwkzButton}/>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`Have a go with the prop types within the playground below`}</MDXTag>
